description:
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job type: PCN Clinical Pharmacist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working Pattern: Full time – 37.5 hrs per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Days/Times: Monday to Friday&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will benefit from this unique opportunity to develop effective communication and strong working relationships across our organisation and will be actively involved in how their role evolves over time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full time post working 37.5 hours per week covering the North Colchester PCN which is made up of the following practices:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mill Road, Bluebell, Highwoods, Lawford and Winstree Surgeries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All flexible offers and working arrangements will be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to find out more information and discuss further, please contact Lara.Rogers@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews to take place: Weds 9th &amp; 16th December&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;We have the right to close the vacancy earlier than the closing date, if we reach the maximum number of applications.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This role is also being advertised on the Essex Primary Care Careers website, please complete only one application, duplications will not be considered.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;NO AGENCIES PLEASE&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Main purpose of job:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To support the effective delivery of patient care in GP practices within a defined Primary Care Network (PCN) by utilising pharmaceutical skills to embed the principles of medicines optimisation within the wider practice teams, ensure safe patient care through regular review and monitoring of patients based on clinical need and support demand management through consultation with patients as appropriate. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clinical Care includes:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run clinics where medicines are the main interventions e.g. anticoagulant monitoring clinics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct spirometry, child immunisation, travel vaccination, diabetic foot checks and NHS Health Checks as well as other roles as required on completion of appropriate training.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct care planning including mental health, admission avoidance schemes and End of Life patients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitoring patients with complex long term conditions such as hypertension, diabetes and COPD, ensuring that medication is optimised, titrated, monitored and complied with.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing clinical advice and expertise on medication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver on and/or oversee relevant aspects of the PCN Directed Enhanced Service (DES).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take a central role in the clinical aspects of shared care protocols, clinical research with medicines, liaison with specialist pharmacists&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the repeat prescribing reauthorisation process by reviewing requests for repeat prescriptions and medicines reaching review dates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To contribute to the reduction of medicine wastage within practices across the &lt;strong&gt;PCN.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Candidate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be a qualified Pharmacist with strong experience within Primary Care and have the following skills / qualifications:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Degree Pharmacy, and registration with the General Pharmaceutical Council&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ideally you will hold or be working towards a postgraduate pharmacy qualification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Post qualification experience in pharmacy (hospital, primary care or community).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ideally be working towards/being an independent prescriber&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Member of the Royal Pharmaceutical Society (RPS)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will have awareness of the breadth of common acute and long term conditions that are likely to be seen in a general medical practice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be able to demonstrate general pharmaceutical skills and knowledge in core areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will be able to plan, manage, monitor, advise and review general care plans for patients with long term conditions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist patients in decisions about prescribed medicines and supporting adherence as per NICE guidance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mature and non-judgemental attitude and be flexible and adaptable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self motivated with excellent communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand the need for patient confidentiality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work as an autonomous practitioner and will be supported by the wider clinical teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must have excellent clinical and leadership skills, be proactive and self-motivated, but most importantly, have a passion for maintaining high standards of care and developing services with the patient at the centre of your service delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;North Colchester PCN has a patient population of approximately 36,700 across 5 practices.  We aim to provide high quality services adhering to principles of best practice, promoting equal opportunities and working positively with diversity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We expect all employees to carry out their duties in a professional manner with a client focus, ensuring that respect and courtesy is shown to them, colleagues, other service providers and all those in contact with the organisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Supporting your work life balance and professional development is important to us, so we will be happy to discuss any requirements for flexible working and offer the following benefits:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Holiday will be 30 days per annum plus bank holidays if these fall on a working day&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Uniform is not provided&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Staff car parking available free of charge&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Eligible to join the NHS Pension scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive salary based on experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supportive and friendly environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working hours&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Peer support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CPD Support with training and development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
